  "reasoning": "The Samsung SSD 860 EVO is missing from the ata_device_blacklist array with the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag. The bug manifests as 20-30 second lockups and timeouts when executing queued TRIM commands (SEND FPDMA QUEUED) on this device. The kernel already has a mechanism to disable queued TRIM for problematic devices via the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM flag, which is checked in ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv() function (line 2218-2221). Similar Samsung models (840 and 850) are already in the blacklist with this flag (lines 4562-4565), but 860 is conspicuously absent. The fix requires adding a blacklist entry for 'Samsung SSD 860*' with the ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM and ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM flags, similar to the existing 840 and 850 entries."
}

